Circus Renz, in which her son played as the ever so cheerful clown, was her lust and her life.  She helped save the circus from destruction several times, including after the shocking deaths of directors Herman and Diana in their car from carbon monoxide poisoning. In her circus career she was a ringmaster.  Behind the scenes, she was also the financial director who faced major challenges several times.  She became a Knight in the Order of Orange-Nassau of which she was very proud.  In her book ‘They won’t get me small’ she describes her adventures with the entire circus family that is now mourning the loss of ‘their mother’.  Clown Milko has shared his grief on social media several times in recent weeks for the approaching end of the brave and unforgettable Anneke.  She was 79 years old. Circus mother Anneke Olivier (79) passed away |  Stars
